    	<h2 style="text-align:center; font-size: 2.5em; color: black; padding-top: 40px;"> Get to Know DR</h2>
    	<p style="width:50%; float: right; padding-right: 50px; line-height: 22px; font-size:1.5em;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; What started over 30 years ago as an idea for a downtown restaurant/microbrewery to combine fresh, handcrafted, made-from-scratch beer and southern food. Today it has become a reality at Peggy & Michael’s Downtown Restaurant/Microbrewery across the south as well as in the heart of the Atlanta, Georgia! This now famous idea of serving up excellent beer and awesome southern food became a reality on July 7, 2016, when the first Peggy & Michael’s Downtown Restaurant/Microbrewery opened its doors in Fulton County, Georgia.<br/><br/>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Obtained later by the famous Dogfish Head, Milton, Delaware Brewing Company in 2015 Peggy & Michael’s Restaurant/Microbrewery currently operates 25 restaurant/microbreweries in the south including not only Georgia, but Texas, Tennessee, Alabama, South Carolina, and Virginia. In addition to the south’s 25 Peggy & Michael’s Downtown Restaurant/Microbreweries 10 will soon operate in Japan. Peggy & Michael’s Restaurant/Microbrewery heritage of supreme beer and delicious southern food along with good old times are now being served fresh each and every day.</p>
